…or create a new repository on the command line
echo "# Docker-Containers" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/nagababudba0999/Docker-Containers.git
git push -u origin main
…or push an existing repository from the command line
git remote add origin https://github.com/nagababudba0999/Docker-Containers.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

-------------------------------
Once you cloned the repo run below command to create image 

docker build -t flask-app .

docker image will be created, you can run the docker image by 

docker run -d flask-app

